<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><refentry version="5.0-subset Scilab" xml:id="imregionalmin" xml:lang="en" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"><refnamediv><refname>imregionalmin</refname><refpurpose>Find local minimum plateaus.</refpurpose></refnamediv><refsynopsisdiv><title>Syntax</title><synopsis>out = imregionalmin(image); out = imregionalmin(image, connectivity)</synopsis></refsynopsisdiv><refsection><title>Parameters</title><variablelist><varlistentry><term>image</term><listitem><para>A non-empty 2D grayscale image.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>connectivity</term><listitem><para>4 or 8. The default is 8.</para></listitem></varlistentry><varlistentry><term>out</term><listitem><para>A boolean mask of pixels equal to their local neighborhood minimum.</para></listitem></varlistentry></variablelist></refsection><refsection><title>Description</title><para><function>imregionalmin</function> marks local minimum plateaus using the selected neighborhood. Border values are replicated.</para></refsection><refsection><title>Examples</title><programlisting><![CDATA[image = uint8([4 2 4; 2 1 2; 4 2 4]); minima = imregionalmin(image); imshow(minima);]]></programlisting></refsection><refsection role="see also"><title>See also</title><simplelist type="inline"><member><link linkend="imregionalmax">imregionalmax</link></member><member><link linkend="imextendedmin">imextendedmin</link></member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>Authors</title><simplelist type="vert"><member>Tan Chin Luh</member></simplelist></refsection><refsection><title>History</title><informaltable border="1"><tr><td>Version</td><td>Description</td></tr><tr><td>5.0.0</td><td>Function introduced in development Step 3.</td></tr></informaltable></refsection></refentry>
